# Vanilla JavaScript

No bundler or npm dependencies. Prefer `assets/js/main.js` after the asset split; until then, keep inline `<script>` at end of `index.html`.

## Public API (preserve unless refactoring)

| Function | Role |
|----------|------|
| `openModal()` | Opens `#quoteModal`, sets `body` overflow hidden |
| `closeModal(e)` | Closes on overlay click (`e.target === e.currentTarget`) |
| `handleSubmit(e)` | Prevents default; mock success UI on form |

Inline handlers in HTML call these: `onclick="openModal()"`, `onsubmit="handleSubmit(event)"`.

## Scroll behavior

```javascript
// #mainNav gets .elevated when scrollY > 40
// #floatCta gets .visible when scrollY > 600
```

## Scroll reveal

- Targets: `.fade-up`
- `IntersectionObserver` with `threshold: 0.1`, adds `.in` once visible

## Marquee (`#marqueeTrack`)

- Pause on card `mouseenter` / `mouseleave` via `.paused` class
- Do not break CSS animation on the track when editing reviews

## Form backend (future)

When integrating a real endpoint:

1. Add `name` on every input/select/textarea
2. Replace mock `handleSubmit` with `fetch` or native `action`/`method`
3. Keep success/error UX consistent with existing button state change

## Style

- Use `const` / arrow functions as in existing code
- Query by ID (`getElementById`) or stable classes — avoid brittle nth-child selectors
